数说疫情0307：中国全力夺武汉，美国染疫州近半。
Counting epidemic 0307: China seized Wuhan, the United States affected nearly half of the state.
徐进。
Xu Jin.
财经杂志                      。
Financial magazine.
财经杂志。
Financial magazine.
《财经》杂志官方微信。
An official letter from Caijing magazine.
《财经》杂志由中国证券市场研究中心主办，1998年创刊，秉承“独立、独家、独到”的新闻理念，以权威性、公正性、专业性报道见长，是政经学界决策者、研究者、管理者的必读刊物。
"Caijing" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was founded in 1998, upholding the news concept of "independence, exclusivity and originality," and providing authoritative, impartial and professional reports.
。
.
国内31个省区市新增确诊降至两位数；全球累计确诊病例已破10万大关；意大利疫情最严重地区医疗资源已消耗殆尽文 |《财经》数据研究员徐进 图 |《财经》视觉中心 编辑 | 郝洲一、国内疫情防控形势继续向好，局面尽在掌控，输入病例占近1/4今日国内简述：国内3月6日报告累计确诊病例80651例，新增99例，排在伊、意、韩、法、德、西等6国之后。
The country's 31 provinces and municipalities have seen double-digit new diagnoses; the global cumulative number of confirmed cases has passed the 100,000 mark; Italy's worst-affected region has exhausted its medical resources; Caijing data researcher Xu Jin-tou and Hao Zhou.
国内非湖北地区本地新增病例仅北京1例。
There was only one case of local new cases in non-Hubei area.
该病例自2月6日起已作为疑似病例治疗排查并集中隔离直至确诊，不会造成进一步传染扩散。
The case has been treated as a suspected case since February 6 and is kept in isolation until confirmed, without further transmission.
湖北非武汉地区连续两日零新增。
Hubei non-Wuhan area added two consecutive days.
武汉新增病例终于回落至两位数！兰州、北京、上海、深圳等口岸境外输入病例24例，局面尽在掌控中。
Wuhan finally back to double-digit cases! Lanzhou, Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen and other ports of entry of 24 cases, the situation is under control.
二、全球疫情扩散仍在加速图1海外新增已经突破3000，比昨日增量高出近1/3，累计病例迅速突破2万，以目前态势，将会很快3万、4万……世卫组织总干事谭德塞3月6日在日内瓦表示，世卫组织继续建议所有国家将控制传播作为最高优先事项。
The spread of the global epidemic is still accelerating. Figure 1 New overseas arrivals have surpassed 3,000, nearly a third higher than yesterday's increase, with a cumulative total of 20,000 cases rapidly surpassing the current trend of 30,000 and 40,000.
迄今为止，世卫组织已收到审查和批准40种诊断试验的申请。
To date, WHO has received applications to review and approve 40 diagnostic tests.
目前有20种疫苗正在研发，许多治疗药物的临床试验正在进行之中。
There are currently 20 vaccines under development, and clinical trials for many therapeutic drugs are under way.
但距离疫苗的最终面试，有专家认为还需12-18个月。
But some experts say it will take another 12 to 18 months before the final interview for the vaccine.
图2这张图今天已经眼花缭乱了，继昨天增加德国之后，法国今天也入榜。
Fig. 2 The picture is dazzling today, and following yesterday's addition of Germany, France is on the list today.
伊朗单日新增破千，该国医疗系统正面临一场巨大考验。
Iran faces a huge test of its health-care system as it adds thousands a day.
伊朗卫生部部长纳马基介绍说，疑似感染者将接受检测，检测结果为阳性的病例将被居家隔离，并收到配给的药物和使用说明。
The suspected cases will be tested and those tested positive will be quarantined at home and given medication and instructions, Health Minister Manouchehr Namaki said.
另据他介绍，伊朗用于新冠病毒检测的医疗机构已达22家，预计下周可达到40家。
He added that Iran has 22 medical institutions for testing the virus and expects to reach 40 next week.
三、美国近半数州出现确诊病例图3目前，全美共有25个州出现确诊病例。
Diagram 3 There are currently 25 confirmed cases in 25 states across the United States.
华盛顿州成为美国新冠病毒疫情重灾区，为做好防疫、保障安全，位于西雅图的华盛顿大学3月6日宣布，该校5万名学生从下周一（3月9日）开始上网课，一直上到3月20日。
WASHINGTON, Mar 9 (Reuters) - Washington University in Seattle announced Monday that 50,000 students at Washington University will start online next Monday and stay there until March 20 to protect themselves from a deadly outbreak of the virus.
美国会通过紧急拨款83亿元抗击疫情，其中的30亿美元，将给美国大药厂开发疗法与疫苗，3亿元用于确保美国公民都能接种疫苗；另外，22亿元用于预防、准备和回应，10亿元投入缓解地方政府与卫生系统的财务压力。
The US will urgently allocate 8.3 billion yuan to fight the epidemic, of which $3 billion will be used to develop treatments and vaccines for major U.S. pharmaceutical companies, $300 million to ensure that all United States citizens are vaccinated, $2.2 billion for prevention, preparedness and response, and $1 billion to ease the financial burden on local governments and health systems.
图4一夜之间，美国又新增84例患者，其中有21例来自“至尊公主”号邮轮，船上约3500人将陆续接受新冠病毒检测。
Fig. 4. Eighty-four new cases were reported overnight in the United States, 21 of them from the MV Supreme Princess, and about 3,500 people on board will be tested for the virus.
邮轮所属公司公主邮轮公司（Princess Cruise Lines）称，目前船上有35人感到不适。
Princess Cruise Lines, a cruise company, said 35 people were not feeling well on board.
首批检测预计24小时内会有结果。
The first tests are expected within 24 hours.
四、韩国将在大邱市展开更大范围的排查图5韩国中央安全对策本部称，大邱普通市民的诊断检查阳性率在9%~10%左右，目前还不能掉以轻心，为了阻止地区社会感染，今后几周必须集中对大邱市民进行诊断检查，致力于发现确诊患者。
The Ministry of Central Security Policy of the Republic of Korea says that the positive rate of diagnosis among the general public in Daegu is between 9% and 10%. In order to prevent social infection in the region, it is necessary to focus on diagnosing Daegu citizens in the coming weeks.
五、意大利伦巴第大区医疗资源耗尽图6德国病例最集中的是北莱茵-威斯特法伦州，已经出现了281例，该州疫情爆发点海恩斯贝格县已关闭所有中小学和幼儿园直到3月15日。
The largest concentration of cases in Germany is in North Rhine-Westphalia, where 281 cases have already occurred, and all schools and kindergartens in Heinsberg County, the epicentre of the outbreak, were closed until 15 March.
法国总理菲利普宣布加强国内疫情最为严重的瓦兹省和上莱茵省的防疫措施，包括关闭中小学和幼儿园以及限制集会等。
French Prime Minister Philippe Philippe announced the strengthening of immunization efforts in the most affected provinces of Vaz and Haute Rhine, including the closure of schools and kindergartens and restrictions on assembly.
他同时表示，法国仍处在遏制病毒在境内扩散的“第二阶段”，“虽然疫情升级不可避免，但法国的卫生系统有能力应对”。
He also said France was still in the "second stage" of containing the spread of the virus within its borders, saying that "while an escalation is inevitable, France's health system is capable of responding."
图7过去24小时，意大利新冠肺炎疫情已从79座城市，蔓延至89座城市，死亡患者197人。
Figure 7 In the past 24 hours, the outbreak of pneumonia in Italy has spread from 79 cities to 89 cities, with 197 deaths.
意大利卫生官员称，意大利头号疫区伦巴第大区约10%的医务工作者已被感染。
Italian health officials say about 10 percent of health workers in Italy's most affected region, Lombardy, have been infected.
目前，当地70%的外科手术已被迫延期，当地其他门诊服务也因调拨人员而将从3月9日后全部暂停。
Currently, 70 per cent of local surgical operations have been postponed and other local outpatient services will be suspended from 9 March owing to the redeployment of personnel.
伦巴第地区的医疗资源已消耗殆尽。
Medical resources in the Lombardy area have been depleted.
意大利是欧洲医疗最为发达的国家之一，每千人约有4.09名执业医师，伦巴第又是意大利经济最为发达的地区，医疗资源最丰富。
Italy is one of the most medically developed countries in Europe, with about 4.09 medical practitioners per 1,000 people, and Lombardy is the most economically developed region in Italy, with the most medical resources.
【特别说明：以上统计，2月28日前为世卫组织官方统计数据，数据截止时间为北京时间每日17时；从2月28日开始，数据由《财经》根据公开资料统计，截止时间为北京时间每日9时】六、全球疫情数字速览：1、【库存200万份试剂】据统计，从检测试剂盒批准上市以来，截至3月5日，中国累计供给1537.4万人份的试剂盒，日均供应量是34.16万人份，目前生产企业的库存还有大约200万人份，完全能够满足湖北省和全国其他地区的检测需求。
According to statistics, before February 28, WHO official statistics are due at 17: 00 daily Beijing time. Starting from Feb. 28, China has supplied 15.374 million doses of reagents per day, with an average daily supply of 341,600 reagents.
2、【美军4人确诊】美国国防部主管卫生事务的助理部长麦卡弗里（Thomas McCaffery）3月6日向众议院证实，美国军队中已有4人确认感染新冠肺炎，另有12例疑似病例。
U.S. Defense Department Assistant Secretary of Health Thomas McCaffery confirmed to the House on March 6 that four people in the U.S. military had confirmed new cases of pneumonia and 12 other suspected cases.
目前美国有9个至10个美军军事基地具备检测能力。
There are currently 9 to 10 U.S. military bases in the United States with detection capability.
3、【第一批援韩物资】中国驻韩国大使邢海明3月6日通报，中国政府决定向韩方提供一批物资援助，包括10万只N95口罩、100万只医用外科口罩、1万套医用防护服，还愿向韩方提供5万人份检测试剂，以支持韩国政府和人民抗击新冠肺炎疫情小结：自1月26日以来最低 ，经历39天的艰苦奋战，武汉的新增病例终于首次降到两位数。
The Chinese Government has decided to provide material assistance to the ROK, including 100,000 N95 masks, 1 million medical surgical masks and 10,000 medical protection suits, and to provide 50,000 medical reagents to the ROK to support the ROK government and people in their fight against the disease.
如今，武汉每日新增确诊病例的80%以上由疑似病例转入，已进入“去存量”的阶段，局面尽在掌控。
Today, Wuhan, more than 80% of the new daily confirmed cases from suspected cases into the stage of "destocking," the situation is under control.
伊朗、意大利等国的疫情核心区医疗资源被严重消耗。
Medical resources have been severely depleted in the core regions of Iran and Italy.
尽管各国政府都在紧急拨款应对疫情，但是否足以控制住疫情蔓延势头，仍待观察。
It remains to be seen whether governments will be able to contain the spread of the epidemic, despite emergency funding allocations.
